                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18200628-83-off459 t18200628-83-crimeloc461"></join>. On the 25th of May, the prisoner came for two pieces of twelve-penny white sarsnet ribbon, for Mr. W. Townsend of Holborn, who is a customer of ours. I asked his name, he said it was Smith, I gave it to him, he went away. I charged him 28 s. and gave him a bill - he came again next day with a written order for more, he was desired to call again as I had suspicion - and on his return we had him apprehended.</p>
